      <procstep>
        <procdesc>Dataset copied from the cd obtained from Washington, DC 2005

Data automated from Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) Flood Insurance Rate Maps (FIRM). Data was interpreted from FEMA and scribed to USGS 1:12,000 quadrangles manuscripts Generalized 100- and 500- year floodplains.

Published digital map was re projected to NAD 83 meters from UTM and clipped  to the DC boundary. No other changes were made.

All DC GIS data is stored and exported in Maryland State Plane coordinates NAD 83 meters.</procdesc>
